# Example Execution → Verification Guard

This rule enforces a hard guard: when running examples in `apps/examples`, if the example execution fails or produces strict-policy errors, do NOT run the verification script. Abort immediately and surface the error.

## Abort Conditions
- Non-zero exit code from example execution
- Log contains `[STRICT-POLICY]` or `[EDGE-ORDER-VIOLATION]`
- Expected output file is missing or empty:
  - `[apps/examples/data/real-workflow-data.json](mdc:apps/examples/data/real-workflow-data.json)`
  - `[apps/examples/data/perfect-playground-data.json](mdc:apps/examples/data/perfect-playground-data.json)` (when applicable)

## Standard Command Template (non-interactive, safe)
Use this pattern whenever running a workflow example followed by verification. It prevents verification when the example fails.

```bash
cd /Users/jungyoun/Documents/dev/robota/packages/workflow/examples && \
FILE=guarded-edge-verification.ts && \
HASH=$(md5 -q "$FILE") && \
OUT=cache/guarded-edge-verification-$HASH-guarded.log && \
echo "▶️ Run example (guarded)..." && \
STATUS=0; npx tsx "$FILE" > "$OUT" 2>&1 || STATUS=$?; \
tail -n 160 "$OUT" | cat; \
if [ "$STATUS" -ne 0 ] || grep -E "\\[STRICT-POLICY\\]|\\[EDGE-ORDER-VIOLATION\\]" "$OUT" >/dev/null; then \
  echo "❌ Aborting verification (example failed or strict-policy violation)."; \
  exit ${STATUS:-1}; \
fi; \
echo "▶️ Verify..." && \
npx tsx utils/verify-workflow-connections.ts | cat
```

## Files Referenced by Verification
- Verification script: `[packages/workflow/examples/utils/verify-workflow-connections.ts](mdc:packages/workflow/examples/utils/verify-workflow-connections.ts)`
- Example entry: `[packages/workflow/examples/guarded-edge-verification.ts](mdc:packages/workflow/examples/guarded-edge-verification.ts)`

## Rationale
- Conserves tokens and time by skipping verification on failed executions
- Aligns with strict no-fallback policy and path-only architecture
- Ensures transparency of failures; errors must be fixed at the source before verification

